This paper proposes a new algorithm for learning accurate low-bit deep neural networks, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on improving the accuracy of DNNs through a new training algorithm. The second likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as DNNs are widely used in image and video processing applications. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as DNNs are a key component of many AI systems. The fourth likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper proposes a new method for training neural networks. The fifth likely category is cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), as low-bit DNNs are critical for embedded applications, and the proposed algorithm can improve their efficiency.
